<br>
I like grouping.  I understand that as a mage I'll have to get a &quot;good grouper&quot; rep.  I think I will be able to - tho never uber <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  - I am a thinking player and very social.  I have played two of the 'trinity&quot; classes in past lives and should be able to chose/control pet.  I also enjoy out of the box groups.  Since I would go insane if solo 100% of my playtime - being able to break into the social scene and get a rep is critical (for me).  YMMV <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I am going to be starting untwinked, with no high level friends.  I won't be using e-bay, dual-boxing or anything else that would help.  I'm bad at trader buy low sell high tactic.  I do have solo time to farm.<br>
<br>
Since much of my playtime will be solo (RL stuff), ability to find nice slow-paced farm/exp spots a must.<br>
<br>
I play East Coast daytime and can't stay up to match Pacific Coast late night raids/groups.  My schedule matches best with Aussies, after that Euro players.<br>
<br>
I've narrowed my choices to two servers, ironically one of the absolute oldest and one of the newest.   Ironically, the older server has more lowbies (as per /who) but my guess is many are twinks/alts and not interested in lowbie exp/groups/social.  These are the two (in case that factors):<br>
<br>
Karana:<br>
About as old and crowded as they come.  Was my first server at release so I'm sentimental about it and one fellow AC2 refugee will restart there as well.  I'd know all of one other untwinked newb and our schedules don't match well.  I do remember a strong Euro-timezone player base tho.  The old economy would be nice to find &quot;junk&quot; fro my untwinked newbie, but what would I sell to even buy junk?  Farm lowend tradeskill items?   Will the social atmosphere be folks mainly locked into their 2-3 year old small cliques with no opportunity for pick up groups and rep. building?  I.E since I'm not already on the list of known group-competent mages - will I be SOL?<br>
<br>
Venril Sathir (UK new).<br>
New, and from /who still fewer lowbies than Karana.  I'll not even know one person.  It says UK server, but the one board I found indicated it was mainly US player base with many TP server guild(s?) who moved as a group on movelog.  New economy will be hard as buyer, better as seller.  Hopefully new folks will be more open to lowbie grouping and forming new guilds/social circles hunting groups etc.  If enough Euro playerbase some of the regular groups might run while I'm able to play even.<br>
<br>
So for a newb, no twink, no PL, cold start mage main who wants to group part-time?<br>
<br>
Old economy server vs. new?<br>
Old server social scene vs. new?<br>
<br>
Is one clearly better? or does it not matter with movelog and so few true newbies? (I'm not really a true newbie either). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2759<br> <font color=#333333>(1/25/03 7:09:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8578.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Start new untwinked mage main on old or new server?</span><hr size=1> My preference, under your circumstances, would be the newest server, even though you are not a skilled trader.  You are more likely to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;grow up&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> with players and characters of your level there, there is more room for you, and aged servers are often top heavy, meaning you will find the upper levels less satisfying due to intense competion for spawns and raid targets.<br>
<br>
If you like to be independent, I would definitely go with the newer server.<br>
